{"title_page": "AirTags", "text_new": "{{Infobox product\n| title = AirTags\n| image = <!-- official promotional images -->\n| image_size = 250\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| manufacturer = [[Apple Inc.]]\n| type = [[Key finder]]\n| inventor = \n| announced = <!-- change this to when Apple first announce it -->\n| first released = <!-- put date here when released -->\n| inception = Accidentally confirmed by Apple April 2, 2020<!-- change this to date of first consumer availability -->\n| available = <!-- change this to \"yes\" after it is available -->\n| last production = <!-- only to be edited when release -->\n| models = <!-- if more types are released -->\n| website = <!-- official link to the AirTags section of the Apple Website -->\n| url = \n| notes = May require [[ultra-wideband|UWB]] support in iOS device\n}}\n'''AirTags''' is a tracking device created by [[Apple Inc.]] in 2019 or 2020, able to act as a [[key finder]]. It was accidentally revealed in April 2020, as a feature in an official Apple product support video showing it supported in the [[Find My iPhone]] user interface.<ref>{{cite news|title=Apple AirTags: What are they and when are they coming?|quote=Apple's rumored tracking tiles will likely be more accurate than Tile devices and be deeply integrated with the Find My app.|first=Leif |last=Johnson|work=[[Macworld]] | date=April 2, 2020|url=https://www.macworld.com/article/3536073/apple-airtags-faq.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Apple accidentally confirms the existence of an unreleased product, AirTags|first=Sarah |last=Perez|date=April 2, 2020|publisher=[[TechCrunch]]|url=https://techcrunch.com/2020/04/02/apple-accidentally-confirms-the-existence-of-an-unreleased-product-airtags/}}</ref><ref>{{citation|publisher=[[CNET]]|title=Apple's rumored stuff-tracking AirTags turn up in new video|quote=It's reportedly just a quick mention in an Apple support video, but it seems to confirm that the Tile-like trackers are indeed in the works.|first=Ry |last=Crist |date=April 2, 2020|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/apples-rumored-stuff-tracking-airtags-turn-up-in-new-video/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|website=[[Tom's Guide]]|title=Apple AirTags 2020 price, release date, news and leaks|first=Kate |last=Kozuch |date=April 3, 2020|quote=Everything we know about the upcoming Apple AirTags key finder|url=https://www.tomsguide.com/news/apple-airtags-2020-price-release-date-news-and-leaks}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=[[International Business Times]]|title=Apple Confirms Existence Of Tile-Like Trackers, AirTags|first=Julio |last=Cachila |date=April 3, 2020|url=https://www.ibtimes.com/apple-confirms-existence-tile-trackers-airtags-2952147}}</ref> The product was first reported to be under development in April 2019, and in January 2020 an analyst said they were expected to be released in Q1 2020.<ref>{{cite news|title=Apple may be planning to launch a new product called 'AirTags' that would help you find lost items like keys or wallets \u2014 here's everything we know so far|work=[[Business Insider]]|first=Lisa |last=Eadicicco |date=February 5, 2020|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/apple-airtags-new-iphone-product-rumors-release-date-features-2020-2}}</ref> Industry watcher ''Redmond Pie'' reported in February, 2020 that [[Asahi Kasei|Asahi Electronics]] was prepared to begin supplying Apple with tens of millions of [[ultra-wideband]] (UWB) parts for the AirTags in the second and third quarters of 2020.<ref>{{cite web|work=Redmond Pie|title=Apple To Ramp Up UWB Chip Production For AirTags In Q2-Q3 2020|first=Oliver |last=Haslam | date=February 19, 2020|url=https://www.redmondpie.com/apple-to-ramp-up-uwb-chip-production-for-airtags-in-q2-q3-2020/}}</ref> Some [[List of iOS devices|iOS devices]] support UWB and are said to be compatible with AirTags.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://appleosophy.com/2020/04/02/airtags-confirmed-in-a-new-apple-support-video/|title=Exclusive: AirTags confirmed in a new Apple Support Video!|date=2020-04-02|website=Appleosophy|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-22}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n[[Category:Internet object tracking]]\n[[Category:Apple Inc. peripherals]]\n[[Category:IPhone accessories]]\n\n\n{{comp-hardware-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox product\n| title = AirTags\n| image = <!-- official promotional images -->\n| image_size = 250\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| manufacturer = [[Apple Inc.]]\n| type = [[Key finder]]\n| inventor = \n| announced = <!-- change this to when Apple first announce it -->\n| first released = <!-- put date here when released -->\n| inception = Accidentally confirmed by Apple April 2, 2020<!-- change this to date of first consumer availability -->\n| available = <!-- change this to \"yes\" after it is available -->\n| last production = <!-- only to be edited when release -->\n| models = <!-- if more types are released -->\n| website = <!-- official link to the AirTags section of the Apple Website -->\n| url = \n| notes = May require [[ultra-wideband|UWB]] support in iOS device\n}}\n'''AirTags''' is a tracking device created by [[Apple Inc.]] in 2019 or 2020, able to act as a [[key finder]]. It was accidentally revealed in April 2020, as a feature in an official Apple product support video showing it supported in the [[Find My iPhone]] user interface.<ref>{{cite news|title=Apple AirTags: What are they and when are they coming?|quote=Apple's rumored tracking tiles will likely be more accurate than Tile devices and be deeply integrated with the Find My app.|first=Leif |last=Johnson|work=[[Macworld]] | date=April 2, 2020|url=https://www.macworld.com/article/3536073/apple-airtags-faq.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Apple accidentally confirms the existence of an unreleased product, AirTags|first=Sarah |last=Perez|date=April 2, 2020|publisher=[[TechCrunch]]|url=https://techcrunch.com/2020/04/02/apple-accidentally-confirms-the-existence-of-an-unreleased-product-airtags/}}</ref><ref>{{citation|publisher=[[CNET]]|title=Apple's rumored stuff-tracking AirTags turn up in new video|quote=It's reportedly just a quick mention in an Apple support video, but it seems to confirm that the Tile-like trackers are indeed in the works.|first=Ry |last=Crist |date=April 2, 2020|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/apples-rumored-stuff-tracking-airtags-turn-up-in-new-video/}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|website=[[Tom's Guide]]|title=Apple AirTags 2020 price, release date, news and leaks|first=Kate |last=Kozuch |date=April 3, 2020|quote=Everything we know about the upcoming Apple AirTags key finder|url=https://www.tomsguide.com/news/apple-airtags-2020-price-release-date-news-and-leaks}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|newspaper=[[International Business Times]]|title=Apple Confirms Existence Of Tile-Like Trackers, AirTags|first=Julio |last=Cachila |date=April 3, 2020|url=https://www.ibtimes.com/apple-confirms-existence-tile-trackers-airtags-2952147}}</ref> The product was first reported to be under development in April 2019, and in January 2020 an analyst said they were expected to be released in Q1 2020.<ref>{{cite news|title=Apple may be planning to launch a new product called 'AirTags' that would help you find lost items like keys or wallets \u2014 here's everything we know so far|work=[[Business Insider]]|first=Lisa |last=Eadicicco |date=February 5, 2020|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/apple-airtags-new-iphone-product-rumors-release-date-features-2020-2}}</ref> Industry watcher ''Redmond Pie'' reported in February, 2020 that [[Asahi Kasei|Asahi Electronics]] was prepared to begin supplying Apple with tens of millions of [[ultra-wideband]] (UWB) parts for the AirTags in the second and third quarters of 2020.<ref>{{cite web|work=Redmond Pie|title=Apple To Ramp Up UWB Chip Production For AirTags In Q2-Q3 2020|first=Oliver |last=Haslam | date=February 19, 2020|url=https://www.redmondpie.com/apple-to-ramp-up-uwb-chip-production-for-airtags-in-q2-q3-2020/}}</ref> Some [[List of iOS devices|iOS devices]] support UWB and are said to be compatible with AirTags.<ref>{{cite web|title=Apple confirms unreleased AirTags in own support video|first=Mike |last=Wuerthele|website=[[AppleInsider]]|date=April 2, 2020|url=https://appleinsider.com/articles/20/04/02/unreleased-airtags-name-spotted-in-apples-own-support-video}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n[[Category:Internet object tracking]]\n[[Category:Apple Inc. peripherals]]\n[[Category:IPhone accessories]]\n\n\n{{comp-hardware-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Hesatter", "label": "safe", "comment": "Corrected citation with original source.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AirTags"}
{"title_page": "Campbellton, New Brunswick", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Campbellton\n| official_name                   = City of Campbellton<br />''Ville de Campbellton''\n| other_name                      = \"The City of Two Coasts\"\n| native_name                     = \n| settlement_type                 = [[List of cities in New Brunswick|City]]\n| motto                           = \n| image_skyline                   = Statue of a huge salmon in Campbellton, New Brunswick - panoramio.jpg\n| imagesize                       = 250 px\n| image_caption                   = Restigouche Sam, with [[Sugarloaf Mountain (New Brunswick)|Sugarloaf Mountain]] in the background\n| image_flag                      = \n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = Campbellton_Logo.svg\n| seal_size                       = 270 px\n| image_shield                    = \n| shield_size                     = \n| city_logo                       = \n| citylogo_size                   = \n| image_map                       = \n| mapsize                         = \n| map_caption                     = \n| image_map1                      = \n| mapsize1                        = \n| map_caption1                    = \n| image_dot_map                   = \n| dot_mapsize                     = \n| dot_map_caption                 = \n| dot_x                           = \n| dot_y                           = \n| pushpin_map                     = New Brunswick\n| pushpin_label_position          = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location within New Brunswick\n| pushpin_mapsize                 = \n| subdivision_type                = [[Country]]\n| subdivision_name                = {{CAN}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Province]]\n| subdivision_name1               = {{NB}}\n| subdivision_type2               = [[County]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Restigouche County, New Brunswick|Restigouche]]\n| subdivision_t